The paper deals with optimization problems in MIMO interference networks, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of polite water-filling, which is a technique for optimizing network resources, and duality, which is a mathematical concept used in optimization problems. These topics are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
